get image tag "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=============================================================

NAME
----

get image tag - An \<img src /\> tag for an image attachment, scaling it down if

SYNOPSIS
--------

An \<img src /\> tag for an image attachment, scaling it down if
requested.

The filter 'get\_image\_tag\_class' allows for changing the class name
for the image without having to use regular expressions on the HTML
content. The parameters are: what WordPress will use for the class, the
Attachment ID, image align value, and the size the image should be.

The second filter 'get\_image\_tag' has the HTML content, which can then
be further manipulated by a plugin to change all attribute values and
even HTML content.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_image_tag( $id, $alt, $title, $align, $size ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Attachment ID.
    Default: *None*

 `$alt` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Image Description for the alt attribute.
    Default: *None*

 `$title` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Image Description for the title attribute.
    Default: *None*

 `$align` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Part of the class name for aligning the image.
    Default: *None*

 `$size` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Default is 'medium'.
    Default: medium

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   HTML IMG element for given image attachment

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_image_tag()` is located in `wp-includes/media.php`

